- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with estimating graph properties, specifically the size of online networks such as Facebook. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a new technique for estimating graph size. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of Random Walk-based techniques for estimating nodal attributes and local graph properties. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with graph theory and estimating graph properties. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also a possible category as the paper deals with online networks and their properties.
